# Internal Links Loop (Strict)

Follow this loop exactly for internal-link insertion tasks. Stack `internal-links-pillar-cluster-loop.mdc` for category pillar/spoke wiring.

1. Create `temp_internal_links_checklist.txt` with one line per article:
   - Format: `- [ ] src/content/blog/<slug>.mdx`
2. Pick the first unchecked article.
3. **Keyword map first:** read target `mainKeyword` and `title` from frontmatter (and pillar registry) before choosing anchors.
4. **Silo targets:** max **4** contextual links to `/blog/*` per article (excluding `/blog/` hub); stricter silo cap until long-form remediate (Scope 08). Remaining paragraph links to `/`, `/about/`, `/services/`, `/blog/`, `/categories/`, `/tags/`, `/contact/`, category/tag hubs.
5. **Density (2026 SSOT):** **3-7** paragraph internal links per **1000 Hebrew words**; target spacing **~1 link per 200-350 words**; never exceed **7/1000**. Hub/category/tag links count toward density totals.
6. **Contextual tier (words >800):** target contextual `/blog/*` links per `computeBlogLinkDensityBounds()` (min capped by silo max 4). Enforced in `content:audit` and when `CONTENT_LINKS_STRICT=1`.
7. Insert links only in **paragraph** prose (not headings, lists, or buttons). **Max one link per `href` per `##` H2 section.**
8. Unique Hebrew anchor per link; unique `href` per article; **max 7 words per anchor**.
9. **Anchor text:** descriptive Hebrew; must include target `mainKeyword` or meaningful title tokens. Ban: `קריאה פנימית`, `קריאה קשורה`, numbered generic series, `קישור פנימי`, `לחץ כאן`, `קרא עוד`, `עמוד זה`, English slug fragments, `click here`, `read more`, `this page`.
10. Do not use the standard 7-nav boilerplate paragraph (`כדי לבנות הקשר רחב` + home/about/services block).
11. **Pillar:** each non-pillar post in a category with `CATEGORY_PILLARS` must link its primary pillar once (anchor uses pillar `mainKeyword` when possible). See pillar-cluster loop.
12. All internal paths use trailing slashes (e.g. `/about/`). Internal links stay crawlable (no `nofollow` on internal).
13. Sync `internalLinks` frontmatter array to match every internal path used in body paragraphs.
14. Run `pnpm run content:audit` for this slug; run `pnpm run links:audit` when graph/orphan checks are needed.
15. Mark article done.

Hard requirements:
- **3-7/1000** paragraph internal links with **200-350** word spacing; **max 7 words** per anchor; **max 4** silo `/blog/*` links (reconcile with density on long posts in remediate pass).
- Log: `[internal-links-loop] step N` or `ERROR`.
- Preserve frontmatter schema; never modify unrelated files.
- Orphan posts (zero inbound blog links) must be fixed before batch complete (`node scripts/remediate-internal-links-batch.mjs`).
